# ============================================================================
#                          DOCKER SERVICE ACCOUNTS CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================
# This file contains account credentials and connection details for all
# Docker-based services used in the SnapLogic Robot Framework test environment.
# 
# IMPORTANT: These credentials are for LOCAL DOCKER INSTANCES ONLY
# - All services run as Docker containers defined in docker-compose.yml files
# - These are NOT production credentials
# - Passwords and credentials here are for local development/testing only
# - Each service has its own Docker container with preconfigured users
#
# HOW IT WORKS:
# 1. Docker Compose starts service containers (databases, message brokers, etc.)
# 2. Each container is pre-configured with the credentials defined below
# 3. Tests use these credentials to connect to the containerized services
# 4. Host names (e.g., oracle-db, postgres-db) are Docker container names
#    that resolve within the Docker network
#
# TO MODIFY:
# 1. Change values in this file
# 2. Restart affected containers: make restart-tools
#
# SECURITY NOTE:
# - This file contains test credentials only
# - Do NOT commit production credentials to this file
# - Use .env.secrets or environment-specific files for sensitive data
# ============================================================================

